title: What to do when an employee dies

heading_context: What to do when an employee dies
chunks.html_content:
You must report a death in the workplace (except in Northern Ireland) to the:

  • police
  • Health and Safety Executive (HSE)

heading_context: What to do when an employee dies
chunks.html_content: Report a workplace death in Northern Ireland to the Health and Safety Executive for Northern Ireland (HSENI).
chunks.plain_content:
What to do when an employee dies
Report a workplace death in Northern Ireland to the Health and Safety Executive for Northern Ireland (HSENI).

heading_context: What to do when an employee dies
chunks.html_content: You must report any deaths or serious injuries, even if the employee is working off-site at the time.
chunks.plain_content:
What to do when an employee dies
You must report any deaths or serious injuries, even if the employee is working off-site at the time.

heading_context: What to do when an employee dies
chunks.html_content:
You must make all outstanding payments when an employee dies.

Put the date they died into the Date of leaving field in your next Full Payment Submission (FPS), and deduct tax using their existing tax code. Use category letter X so that you do not deduct National Insurance. Do not produce a P45.
chunks.plain_content:
What to do when an employee dies
You must make all outstanding payments when an employee dies.
Put the date they died into the Date of leaving field in your next Full Payment Submission (FPS), and deduct tax using their existing tax code. Use category letter X so that you do not deduct National Insurance. Do not produce a P45.

heading_context: What to do when an employee dies
chunks.html_content: Payments to a person who has died are usually made to the personal representative or executor of that persons estate.
chunks.plain_content:
What to do when an employee dies
Payments to a person who has died are usually made to the personal representative or executor of that persons estate.

heading_context: What to do when an employee dies
chunks.html_content:
If an employee dies and you did not report it in the right FPS, follow the guidance for when an employee leaves.

If you need to pay someone after youve sent an FPS with their Date of leaving (the date they died):

  • use tax code 0T on a week 1 or month 1 basis
  • include their Date of leaving and put Yes in the Payment after leaving indicator field in your FPS
  • choose H - Correction to an earlier submission in the Late payment reason field
  • update the year-to-date figures - or if its a new tax year, make sure the year-to-date figures only include the additional payment
chunks.plain_content:

Making a late payment
If you make a mistake
If an employee dies and you did not report it in the right FPS, follow the guidance for when an employee leaves.
If you need to pay someone after youve sent an FPS with their Date of leaving (the date they died):

  use tax code 0T on a week 1 or month 1 basis
  include their Date of leaving and put Yes in the Payment after leaving indicator field in your FPS

  choose H - Correction to an earlier submission in the Late payment reason field
  update the year-to-date figures - or if its a new tax year, make sure the year-to-date figures only include the additional payment

heading_context: What to do when an employee dies
chunks.html_content:
You must make all outstanding payments when someone receiving your company pension dies.

Put the date they died in the Date of leaving field in your next Full Payment Submission (FPS), and work out their final pension payment.

Use their existing tax code unless its a new tax year by the time you pay them.

If its a new tax year and you have not reported their Date of leaving (the date they died) on an FPS yet, use their new tax code. Otherwise, use tax code 0T on a week 1 or month 1 basis and put Yes in the Payment after leaving indicator field in your FPS.
chunks.plain_content:
What to do when an employee dies
Working out tax
You must make all outstanding payments when someone receiving your company pension dies.
Put the date they died in the Date of leaving field in your next Full Payment Submission (FPS), and work out their final pension payment.
Use their existing tax code unless its a new tax year by the time you pay them.
If its a new tax year and you have not reported their Date of leaving (the date they died) on an FPS yet, use their new tax code. Otherwise, use tax code 0T on a week 1 or month 1 basis and put Yes in the Payment after leaving indicator field in your FPS.

heading_context: What to do when an employee dies
chunks.html_content: Payments to a person who has died are usually made to the personal representative or executor of that persons estate.
chunks.plain_content:

heading_context: What to do when an employee dies
If you pay someone after their death
chunks.html_content:
If youve made a pension payment to someone after they died (for example because you were told about their death late), you should get the overpayment back from their executor.

Put the pensioners Date of leaving (the date they died) on your next FPS, and choose H - Correction to an earlier submission in the Late reporting reason field.

If you do not know the date they died, put the date of their final pension payment as their Date of leaving.

Amend the year-to-date figures if you get the overpayment back.

If its a new tax year by the time you find out a pensioner has died:

  • put 0.00 in the year-to-date figures for pay and tax in your FPS
  • send either an Earlier Year Update (EYU) or an FPS with the correct year to date figures for the previous year
chunks.plain_content:
What to do when an employee dies
If you pay someone after their death
If youve made a pension payment to someone after they died (for example because you were told about their death late), you should get the overpayment back from their executor.
Put the pensioners Date of leaving (the date they died) on your next FPS, and choose H - Correction to an earlier submission in the Late reporting reason field.
If you do not know the date they died, put the date of their final pension payment as their Date of leaving.
Amend the year-to-date figures if you get the overpayment back.
If its a new tax year by the time you find out a pensioner has died:

  put 0.00 in the year-to-date figures for pay and tax in your FPS

  send either an Earlier Year Update (EYU) or an FPS with the correct year to date figures for the previous year
